snippet.textDisplay: In my personal opinion, I love Hannah and Peter together. I think they both still love each other. Just look at how emotional they both are in this moment. The show may have set this up for ratings, but I only think they included this in the show because they both still had feelings. I watched all of Colton and Hannah’s season, and I truly think Hannah was confused when it came to her final 3. Colton was dead set that he wanted Cassie and wasn’t willing to settle. Hannah, you could see, was in distress and emotional on the day of her final rose ceremony, because she was conflicted and didn’t want to let anyone go. Peter was the only guy she slept with, and maybe she felt they lacked a true connection for that. And you could tell she only picked Jed because she was comfortable, they didn’t have a pure and genuine connection like she did with both Tyler and Peter. However, I feel her comfort with Jed left her feeling scared and uneasy about starting a relationship with Peter and Tyler. After picking Jed and finding out that he practically cheated on her and his girlfriend back home, she realized she messed up. I truly think she thought she was in love with Jed, when all along she was truly in love with Tyler and Peter and didn’t know what her heart wanted. The girl is allowed to be confused or second guess a decision she made. She felt the pressure of the show. She saw Peter was the next Bachelor and that’s why she didn’t reach out to Peter knowing he was keeping his options open while Tyler was reaching out. But, you could tell there were feelings on both Peter and Hannah’s end at the finale live show. She couldn’t have expected Peter to make the effort to reach out to her, when she slept with him the night before, made him believe he was the one, and then send him home. She ended things with him. I understand both point of views. Hannah picked Jed, then asked Tyler out, and then when that didn’t seem to work out, she suddenly wants Peter back. And Peter deserves this opportunity to find love and not be someone’s third choice. But I don’t think that is what he is to her. I think she thought she was over him, or was trying to move forward knowing he was the Bachelor, but then seeing him as the Bachelor and reuniting with him brought back nostalgia and old memories and feelings. They both truly aren’t over each other even though they thought they were. However, it isn’t fair to the whole house of women who are waiting to find their potential husband, but let’s not act like we haven’t once thought we were over someone before until something triggers us and brings those old feelings back. Peter and Hannah probably haven’t spoken in months until the show started filming and seeing each other triggered something. My guess is that Peter goes back to the house and resumes with dating and gives it a fair shot, while Hannah goes home because she was in DWTS when this was filming. Once Peter gets to his final 2 girls, he feels conflicted because he doesn’t feel a strong connection with either of them and knows he still feels for Hannah. He goes home to get advice from his parents and when they see that he isn’t happy, and that Hannah is who makes him happy, they tell him to go get her. That’s why his mom was crying, (because she wouldn’t be crying had it not been an emotional discussion), and that’s when she says “bring her home to us.” They loved Hannah on Peter’s hometown visit. In the end, Peter doesn’t get engaged to anyone and he proposes to or asks Hannah out at the live show and that’s why there aren’t any spoilers on how this season ends. I’m rooting for them all season. After this, I can’t really see Peter being serious about anyone in the house or willing to commit to anyone but Hannah.

snippet.textDisplay: The overall problem going here between Peter and Hannah B is that they have already connected on both a emotional and physical (in biblical sense BTW on multiple occasions) level.  At the end of the day, this could very well be a airing out of what was left unsaid and closing that door. However; the ball is now in Peter's court to tell Hannah no hard feeling but he is moving on.  With Peter being confused, one thing is very clear here.  If Hannah boldly tells Peter can she get another chance with him, I see him re-opening the door. Why would he do it?  Because he's not over her.
